description:
Department of Chemistry, University of Delhi, Delhi-110 007 

  Manuscript received 2 January 1979. revised 5 June 1979, accepted 6 October 1979  

  &nbsp; Salicylaldebyde hydrazone (SH) has been recommended as a chromogenic reagent for the spectrophotometric determination of palladium(lI) and osmium(VIII) in&nbsp;presence of each other and several other diverse ions. SH forms 1:2 and 1:1 complexes with palladium and osmium respectively. The complexes show maximum absorbance at 425 nm and 430 am in the  \(p\) H ranges 3.0 to 5.0 and 9.5 to 10.0 respec&shy;tively. The colour systems obey Beer&#39;s law upto 21 ppm and 19 7 ppm&nbsp;&nbsp;respectively. The sensitivites of the colour reactions are 0.02  &micro; g/cm 2 &nbsp;and 0.06  &micro; g/cm&#39; for palladium and osmium respectively. &nbsp;  

 &nbsp;

